---
/**
 * context-engineering 0005 · Figure 3 — the generic production context pipeline
 * (ingest → index/store → retrieve → assemble → guardrails → LLM → log).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the
 * footnote <sup>). Standalone .astro component (see Fig1 for the rationale).
 * Carries its own <defs> for the markers it references — #arw, #arwM, #arwR,
 * #arwG.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 660 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A production context pipeline from ingest through guardrails to the LLM, with logging."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="330" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Every production agent is this pipeline</text
        >
        <!-- stages -->
        <rect x="14" y="40" width="78" height="40" rx="7" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
        ></rect><text
            x="53"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">ingest</text
        >
        <rect x="106" y="40" width="86" height="40" rx="7" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"
        ></rect><text
            x="149"
            y="60"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">index /</text
        ><text x="149" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >store</text
        >
        <rect x="206" y="40" width="86" height="40" rx="7" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
        ></rect><text
            x="249"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">retrieve</text
        >
        <rect x="306" y="40" width="86" height="40" rx="7" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
        ></rect><text
            x="349"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">assemble</text
        >
        <rect x="406" y="40" width="92" height="40" rx="7" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text
            x="452"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">guardrails</text
        >
        <rect x="512" y="40" width="64" height="40" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="544"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">LLM</text
        >
        <rect x="590" y="40" width="56" height="40" rx="7" fill="#efe7f0" stroke="#111110"
        ></rect><text
            x="618"
            y="64"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">log</text
        >
        <!-- arrows -->
        <line x1="92" y1="60" x2="104" y2="60" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="192" y1="60" x2="204" y2="60" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="292" y1="60" x2="304" y2="60" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line x1="392" y1="60" x2="404" y2="60" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line x1="498" y1="60" x2="510" y2="60" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="576" y1="60" x2="588" y2="60" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <text
            x="330"
            y="112"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#b5179e"
            >The magenta stages — retrieve &amp; assemble — are where data type dictates the
            mechanism.</text
        >
        <text x="330" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >Guardrails defend against poisoned/injected context; the log makes the whole call
            auditable.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The pipeline is constant; the <em>retrieve</em> stage changes per agent. Get that one stage wrong
        for the data type and no amount of model or prompt fixes it.<sup
            ><a href="#s8" id="r8">8</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
